    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tearing Across Brooklyn Bridge</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lucy Garnett and Barbara Brousal letters on Sarah Shey's March 25 New York Observed essay on driving fast across Brooklyn Bridge</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I couldn't believe that any article would espouse driving 10 to 12 times across the Brooklyn Bridge for pure pleasure (''Her Ride to Nowhere,'' by Sarah Shey, New York Observed, March 25).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I couldn't believe that any article would espouse driving 10 to 12 times across the Brooklyn Bridge for pure pleasure (''Her Ride to Nowhere,'' by Sarah Shey, New York Observed, March 25).</p>
        <p>To read that the driver ''smashed down the accelerator'' and ''attacked the 1.5-mile route with exhaust streaking behind'' horrified me as a longtime resident of Lower Manhattan near the bridge. Vehicular traffic is a serious problem in this neighborhood.</p>
        <p>Lucy Garnett  Lower Manhattan</p>
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Instead of burning fossil fuel for the fun of it and sending plumes of exhaust up to the vaunted Brooklyn Bridge walkway, I suggest that Sarah Shey buy a sturdy three-speed bicycle, bolt on a child seat for her son, and really cruise the bridge -- in all its wind-in-the-hair, expansive-views glory.</p>
        <p>Barbara Brousal  Brooklyn Heights</p>
      </block>
